    "client_msg_id": "36f25657-5c2d-4218-8fbb-b5c3ed547b14",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "In the original version of a system I work on, I let users define pitches using names (c5 etc.) or scale indices. In the new version, I only use scale indices. Western note names and midi numbers ignore most interesting tuning systems, and scale indices are generally easier to use when you want higher levels of abstraction surrounding harmony (chord changes etc.)",
    "user": "UE0H4170F",
    "ts": "1601926247.016700",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
